## Best Practices

1. **Consistency**: Use defined color palette only
2. **Spacing**: Standard scale (4, 8, 12, 16, 24, 32px)
3. **Typography**: Inter font, defined text sizes
4. **Shadows**: Corporate shadows only
5. **Borders**: gray-200/300 subtle, border-2 + #2E5AAC emphasis
6. **Transitions**: Always include (200ms default)
7. **Focus States**: Required for accessibility
8. **Responsive**: Mobile-first approach
9. **Gradients**: Inline styles, consistent direction (135deg diagonal, `to right` horizontal)
10. **White on Gradients**: Always use white text

### Inline Styles vs Tailwind

**Inline Styles**: Gradients, brand colors not in Tailwind (#2E5AAC), emphasis borders, semi-transparent backgrounds, dynamic grid templates

**Tailwind Classes**: Spacing/sizing/layout, typography (except hex colors), responsive, state variants, forvis-* palette colors, shadows

### CSS Classes

Prefer predefined (globals.css): `.btn-primary`, `.btn-secondary`, `.card`, `.card-hover`, `.input-field`, `.animate-fadeIn`, `.animate-scaleIn`

## Avoid

❌ Arbitrary values (except gradients/brand colors) ❌ New color schemes ❌ Default Tailwind shadows ❌ Bold everywhere (font-bold on gradients, font-medium on standard) ❌ Inconsistent spacing ❌ Tailwind for gradients ❌ Black text on gradients ❌ Heavy borders everywhere

## Summary

**Key Principles**: Gradients prominent (headers, stats, emphasis), Brand blue central (#2E5AAC), Visual hierarchy through gradients (darker = important), Inline styles for brand consistency, Grid-based layouts (CSS Grid for tables), Professional aesthetic (clean, corporate), Accessibility maintained (focus states, color contrast, semantic HTML)
